ZH: 我暗自告诉自己要保持冷静。
EN: I secretly tell myself to stay calm.

ZH: 她暗自庆幸自己没有做出愚蠢的决定。
EN: She secretly feels lucky that she didn't make a foolish decision.

ZH: 他暗自后悔没有早点完成作业。
EN: He secretly regrets not finishing his homework earlier.

ZH: 她暗自希望能够得到更多的机会。
EN: She secretly hopes to get more opportunities.

ZH: 我暗自打算在下个月开始一项新的计划。
EN: I secretly plan to start a new project next month.

ZH: 他暗自痛苦地回忆起过去的失败。
EN: He secretly and painfully recalls past failures.

ZH: 她暗自竖起大拇指，表示赞赏。
EN: She secretly gives a thumbs up to show her approval.

ZH: 我暗自腹诽他的决定是错误的。
EN: I secretly criticize his decision as being wrong.

ZH: 他暗自拿出钱包，准备付账。
EN: He secretly takes out his wallet, ready to pay.

ZH: 她暗自想着明天要穿什么衣服。
EN: She secretly thinks about what clothes to wear tomorrow.

ZH: 我们暗自觉得他的行为很奇怪。
EN: We secretly find his behavior strange.

ZH: 他暗自决定不再回答她的问题。
EN: He secretly decides not to answer her questions anymore.

ZH: 她暗自微笑，对他的鼓励表示感激。
EN: She secretly smiles, grateful for his encouragement.

ZH: 我们暗自祈祷能够平安度过这次考试。
EN: We secretly pray to pass the exam safely.

ZH: 他暗自嘲笑自己的错误判断。
EN: He secretly mocks his own wrong judgment.

ZH: 她暗自希望能和他成为朋友。
EN: She secretly wishes to become friends with him.

ZH: 我们暗自庆祝准时完成了任务。
EN: We secretly celebrate for completing the task on time.

ZH: 他暗自想到了一个好点子。
EN: He secretly comes up with a good idea.

ZH: 她暗自疑惑他的行为原因是什么。
EN: She secretly wonders what the reason behind his behavior is.

ZH: 我们暗自羡慕他的天赋和才华。
EN: We secretly envy his talent and ability.
